ZH: 戴帽子可以防止头晒黑。
EN: Wearing a hat can prevent your head from getting sunburned.

ZH: 她戴着一顶粉色的帽子。
EN: She is wearing a pink hat.

ZH: 我的帽子配不上我的新外套。
EN: My hat does not match my new coat.

ZH: 这顶帽子太大了，不适合我。
EN: This hat is too big, it doesn't fit me.

ZH: 爸爸在户外工作时总是戴着帽子。
EN: Dad always wears a hat when working outdoors.

ZH: 这家店里有各种各样的帽子。
EN: This store has all kinds of hats.

ZH: 这顶帽子是用羊毛做的。
EN: This hat is made of wool.

ZH: 我找不到我的帽子，它可能掉在车里了。
EN: I can't find my hat, it might have fallen in the car.

ZH: 我想给他送一顶帽子作为生日礼物。
EN: I want to give him a hat as a birthday present.

ZH: 去沙滩一定要带上帽子和太阳镜。
EN: Always bring a hat and sunglasses to the beach.

ZH: 她把头发盘起来，戴着一顶大草帽。
EN: She pinned up her hair and put on a big straw hat.

ZH: 我的帽子被大风吹走了。
EN: My hat was blown away by the strong wind.

ZH: 这顶帽子很时髦，很适合你。
EN: This hat is very stylish, it suits you well.

ZH: 她在帽子上缝了一朵花。
EN: She sewed a flower on her hat.

ZH: 我的帽子跟我的鞋子颜色相配。
EN: My hat matches the color of my shoes.

ZH: 她戴着一顶遮阳帽，看上去很阳光。
EN: She wore a sun hat and looked very radiant.

ZH: 那个帽子看上去很贵。
EN: That hat looks expensive.

ZH: 这顶帽子的形状很特别。
EN: The shape of this hat is very unique.

ZH: 这家店里有各式各样的帽子供选择。
EN: This store has a variety of hats to choose from.

ZH: 在冬天，戴上毛线帽是很重要的。
EN: It's important to wear a knit hat in winter.
